t = int(input())
for i in range(t):
    n = int(input())
    speeds = list(map(int, input().split()))
    stack = [speeds[0]]
    count = 1
    for j in range(1, n):
        while stack and speeds[j] <= stack[-1]:
            stack.pop()
        stack.append(speeds[j])
        count += len(stack) == 1
    print(count)
